label.value: RCE1 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in the modulation of protein prenylation.

label.value: RCE1 wt Allele

value.value: Human RCE1 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 11q13 and is approximately 4 kb in length. This allele, which encodes CAAX prenyl protease 2 protein, plays a role in the regulation of protein prenylation.

label.value: CAAX Prenyl Protease 2

value.value: CAAX prenyl protease 2 (329 aa, ~36 kDa) is encoded by the human RCE1 gene. This protein is involved in the removal of prenylated peptides from proteins.

label.value: VLDLR Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in both lipoprotein endocytosis and reelin signaling.

label.value: VLDLR wt Allele

value.value: Human VLDLR wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 9p24 and is approximately 33 kb in length. This allele, which encodes very low-density lipoprotein receptor protein, is involved in lipoprotein metabolism and the reelin signaling pathway. Mutation of the gene is associated with cerebellar hypoplasia and mental retardation with or without quadrupedal locomotion 1.

label.value: Very Low-Density Lipoprotein Receptor

value.value: Very low-density lipoprotein receptor (873 aa, ~96 kDa) is encoded by the human VLDLR gene. This protein plays a role in the modulation of both reeling signaling and lipoprotein endocytosis.

label.value: HTR2C Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in neurotransmitter-dependent G protein-coupled receptor signaling.

label.value: HTR2C wt Allele

value.value: Human HTR2C wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of Xq23 and is approximately 326 kb in length. This allele, which encodes 5-hydroxytryptamine receptor 2C protein, plays a role in serotonin binding and signaling. This gene undergoes RNA deamination at sites designated A, B, C-prime, E, C, and D; RNA editing at sites C, D and C-prime may be associated with depression.

label.value: 5-Hydroxytryptamine Receptor 2C

value.value: 5-hydroxytryptamine receptor 2C (458 aa, ~52 kDa) is encoded by the human HTR2C gene. This protein is involved in serotonin-mediated neurotransmission pathways.

label.value: Exceptional Response

value.value: An achievement of either a complete disease response, or a partial disease response of at least 6 months duration in a trial or treatment where the overall response rate is less than 10 percent.

label.value: Gemcitabine/R115777
SLC2A3 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in facilitated transport of glucose.

label.value: SLC2A3 wt Allele

value.value: Human SLC2A3 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 12p13.3 and is approximately 17 kb in length. This allele, which encodes solute carrier family 2, facilitated glucose transporter member 3 protein, is involved in glucose transport.

label.value: Solute Carrier Family 2, Facilitated Glucose Transporter Member 3

value.value: Solute carrier family 2, facilitated glucose transporter member 3 (496 aa, ~54 kDa) is encoded by the human SLC2A3 gene. This protein plays a role in the transport of glucose.

label.value: SLC16A11 Gene

value.value: This gene is involved in transport of carboxylates.

label.value: SLC16A11 wt Allele

value.value: Human SLC16A11 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 17p13.1 and is approximately 2 kb in length. This allele, which encodes monocarboxylate transporter 11 protein, plays a role in monocarboxylate transport. Variation of the gene is associated with susceptiblility to non-insulin dependent diabetes mellitus.

label.value: Monocarboxylate Transporter 11

value.value: Monocarboxylate transporter 11 (471 aa, ~48 kDa) is encoded by the human SLC16A11 gene. This protein is involved in the mediation of monocarboxylate transport.

label.value: IFI16 Gene

value.value: This gene plays a role in transcriptional regulation, cell differentiation and immune response-mediated programmed cell death.

label.value: IFI16 wt Allele

value.value: Human IFI16 wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 1q22 and is approximately 55 kb in length. This allele, which encodes gamma-interferon-inducible protein 16, is involved in both transcriptional regulation and immunity-mediated cell death.

label.value: Gamma-Interferon-Inducible Protein 16

value.value: Gamma-interferon-inducible protein 16 (785 aa, ~88 kDa) is encoded by the human IFI16 gene. This protein plays a role in both immune response-mediated programmed cell death and transcriptional regulation.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage I Noncutaneous Childhood Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage I: Involvement of a single lymph node region (I); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in the absence of any lymph node involvement (IE).

label.value: Amifostine/Carboplatin/Etoposide/Ifosfamide
Ann Arbor Stage II Noncutaneous Childhood Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage II: Involvement of two or more lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (II); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in association with regional lymph node involvement with or without involvement of other lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (IIE).

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage III Noncutaneous Childhood Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage III: Involvement of lymph node regions on both sides of the diaphragm (III), which also may be accompanied by extralymphatic extension in association with adjacent lymph node involvement (IIIE) or by involvement of the spleen (IIIS) or both (IIIE,S).

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage IV Noncutaneous Childhood Anaplastic Large Cell Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage IV: Diffuse or disseminated involvement of one or more extralymphatic organs, with or without associated lymph node involvement; or isolated extralymphatic organ involvement in the absence of adjacent regional lymph node involvement, but in conjunction with disease in distant site(s); or any involvement of the liver or bone marrow, lungs (other than by direct extension from another site), or cerebrospinal fluid.

label.value: Masaoka-Koga Stage II

value.value: The tumor shows invasion into the capsule.

label.value: Masaoka-Koga Stage IV

value.value: The tumor shows metastasis throughout the pleural and/or pericardial spaces or metastasis to distant sites.

label.value: Stage IVA Thyroid Gland Follicular Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IVA includes: (T4a, N0, M0); (T4a, N1a, M0); (T1, N1b, M0); (T2, N1b, M0); (T3, N1b, M0); (T4a, N1b, M0). T4a: Moderately advanced local disease. Tumor of any size extending beyond the thyroid gland capsule to invade subcutaneous soft tissues, larynx, trachea, esophagus, or recurrent laryngeal nerve. T1: Tumor size 2 cm or less in greatest dimension, limited to the thyroid gland. T2: Tumor more than 2 cm but not more than 4 cm in greatest dimension, limited to the thyroid gland. T3: Tumor more than 4 cm in greatest dimension and limited to the thyroid gland, or tumor of any size with minimal extrathyroid extension (e.g., extension to sternothyroid muscle or perithyroid soft tissues). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1a: Metastasis to pretracheal, paratracheal or prelaryngeal/Delphian lymph nodes (Level VI lymph nodes). N1b: Metastasis to unilateral, bilateral or contralateral cervical (Levels I, II, III, IV, or V) or retropharyngeal or superior mediastinal lymph nodes (Level VII). M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVB Thyroid Gland Follicular Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IVB includes: T4b, Any N, M0. T4b: Very advanced disease. Tumor invades prevertebral fascia or encases carotid artery or mediastinal vessels. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVC Thyroid Gland Follicular Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IVC includes: Any T, Any N, M1. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVA Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IVA includes: (T4a, N0, M0); (T4a, N1a, M0); (T1, N1b, M0); (T2, N1b, M0); (T3, N1b, M0); (T4a, N1b, M0). T4a: Moderately advanced local disease. Tumor of any size extending beyond the thyroid gland capsule to invade subcutaneous soft tissues, larynx, trachea, esophagus, or recurrent laryngeal nerve. T1: Tumor size 2 cm or less in greatest dimension, limited to the thyroid gland. T2: Tumor more than 2 cm but not more than 4 cm in greatest dimension, limited to the thyroid gland. T3: Tumor more than 4 cm in greatest dimension and limited to the thyroid gland, or tumor of any size with minimal extrathyroid extension (e.g., extension to sternothyroid muscle or perithyroid soft tissues). N0: No regional lymph node metastasis. N1a: Metastasis to pretracheal, paratracheal or prelaryngeal/Delphian lymph nodes (Level VI lymph nodes). N1b: Metastasis to unilateral, bilateral or contralateral cervical (Levels I, II, III, IV, or V) or retropharyngeal or superior mediastinal lymph nodes (Level VII). M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Stage IVB Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IVB includes: T4b, Any N, M0. T4b: Very advanced disease. Tumor invades prevertebral fascia or encases carotid artery or mediastinal vessels. M0: No distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

label.value: Cyclophosphamide/Cytarabine/Methotrexate
Stage IVC Thyroid Gland Papillary Carcinoma AJCC v7

value.value: Stage IVC includes: Any T, Any N, M1. M1: Distant metastasis. (AJCC 7th ed.)

value.value: Stage IIIA includes: (T1-T2, N1/N1c, M0); (T1, N2a, M0). T1: Tumor invades submucosa. T2: Tumor invades muscularis propria. N1: Metastasis in 1-3 regional lymph nodes.
